    {
      "id": "PopularPost186718",
      "post_content": "This card's rating is kind of low... Considering not much feedback either...\n  \n   \nWell here is some food for thought. 1/3 body for 2cmc is really not too bad. Having 3 toughness will come in handy and may allow this guy to block something and still throw his absorb at another source. Not to mention this little cleric may force an opponent to use a removal spell, especially if combined with [Mother of Runes](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mother of Runes). Now any fattie, or even direct burn can be absorbed easily. Redirect your damage to beacon, give beacon protection from the color of the damage. You can even absorb the mighty [progenitus](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=progenitus) with this combo, you don't need to sac anything or tap any mana for these abilities either.\n  \n   \nI guess I will continue by adding; White has so many 1 (cmc) or 2 (cmc) spells that can easily amplify this cleric. Whether your looking for protection from a color, or reviving this with something like [Order of Whiteclay](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Order of Whiteclay). I will not say ... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Internet_decks_lame",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost186718\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_post\">This card's rating is kind of low...  Considering not much feedback either...\r<br/> <br/>Well here is some food for thought.  1/3 body for 2cmc is really not too bad.  Having 3 toughness will come in handy and may allow this guy to block something and still throw his absorb at another source.  Not to mention this little cleric may force an opponent to use a removal spell, especially if combined with <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Mother of Runes\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mother of Runes\">Mother of Runes</a>.  Now any fattie, or even direct burn can be absorbed easily.  Redirect your damage to beacon, give beacon protection from the color of the damage.  You can even absorb the mighty <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"progenitus\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=progenitus\">progenitus</a> with this combo, you don't need to sac anything or tap any mana for these abilities either.\r<br/> <br/>I guess I will continue by adding; White has so many 1 (cmc) or 2 (cmc) spells that can easily amplify this cleric.  Whether your looking for protection from a color, or reviving this with something like <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Order of Whiteclay\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Order of Whiteclay\">Order of Whiteclay</a>.  I will not say ... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 186718)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleRep